When you push a commit containing something like “{{{fixes BCLOUD-9}}}” all “plain text formatting” turns into one line which is much less readable. Example message:

{{{\\
@aurum/diff: Added AuDiff FVdiff mapping. Ref BCLOUD-6\\
@aurum/cmdutils: Made last argument to getrrf non-numeric and thus more understandable\\
}}}\\
And how it appears in the issue comments:

@aurum/diff: Added AuDiff FVdiff mapping. Ref BCLOUD-6\\
@aurum/cmdutils: Made last argument to getrrf non-numeric and thus more understandable

Automatically adding “**{{{*” before commit message and “*}}}**” after will fix this problem.

